name: Ikan Bakar Alas Purwo Gunung salak
address: Jl. Gunung Salak No.133, Kerobokan, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Amazing place to visit when you don‚Äôt want to go to Jimbaran! All the seafood was super fresh, their spices and sambal 9/10! The place is clean and very spacious! Don‚Äôt forget to order their es kelapa muda
review 2:
Brought here by a local friend as we wanted an authentic experience. Through and through a local seafood place away from the main tourist areas. The price and atmosphere is very local and so is the taste. We ordered grilled fish, clams, prawns, vegetables and a very nice seafood stew.

The seafood all tasted fresh and the sauce layered on top was savoury, sweet and smoky at the same time. The clams stew was amazing as well, tasted a little sour and spicy.
review 3:
Amazing local bbq seafood restaurant in Kerobokan. Dinned in on a Saturday night the restaurant was full. Friendly service & food arrived quickly. We ordered whole snapper, lots of prawns & some squid. Marinade/ sauce was delicious, fish  & prawns cooked perfect, juicy.
Highly recommend & will return!
review 4:
A nice local place that serves good selection of seafood with reasonable price.

The food will be cooked on order, thus you have to wait a little, but they are freshly cooked when served.

However I noticed the quality can be vary depending on who cooks it or how busy they are. But in general, it is good.
review 5: The food is delicious especially ke4ang saus padang

name: Taulan Social Hideout
address: Jl. Pengubengan Kauh, Kerobokan Kelod, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: I bring my two daughters and their Nannie‚Äôs here every week and it‚Äôs been absolutely amazing! The drinks are always refreshing the staff are always on hand ready to help with absolutely anything. The staff really make this place worth the travel! Highly recommend for parents and Nannie‚Äôs looking for somewhere with a pool and playground for the little ones.
review 2: Before coming to this villa I read some reviews and was hesitant but WOW! I am so glad this is the resort we chose. The service has been absolutely incredible all the staff have gone above and beyond for us. We stayed with our 9 month old baby, and they were so accommodating. The room was amazing so clean as well as all the facilities and pools. The food was some of the best we had in Bali and cocktails were fantastic! There is shops in walking distances as well as cafes and restaurants. I can‚Äôt stress enough how amazing the staff were though it really made our trip. Yes the traffic is a little loud but it didn‚Äôt stop us or our baby from getting a full night rest, regardless where you stay you will have noise from the traffic but I‚Äôm so glad we chose here. Would recommend to anyone visiting Bali wanting a reliable, private, hidden gem.
review 3:
Just for lunch with a friend it‚Äôs a great place, lots of space and a well-priced menu.

However, for group reservations they clearly have no system and very poor communication.

Things that went wrong:
- they set up the wrong table for me and my guests (I had very clearly described which table I wanted)
- without asking me, waiters had decided for themselves to put everyone‚Äôs orders on separate bills (they asked their names when ordering; I didn‚Äôt realise this until several people had already left and paid their own bill. I had wanted to pay all or at least part of everyone‚Äôs bill but staff never discussed this with me, very disappointing and not how I wanted to treat my guests)
- I was made to pay a deposit of 1jt to make the reservation 10 days prior. No problem. After everyone had left I was asked to pay my leftover bill, again no problem (but already disappointed they had let all my guests pay their own full bills). Then I asked for my deposit back, or to take my bill off of it. Staff looked at me puzzled, no one seemed to know I had paid a deposit, I had to show them proof of the transfer. Then they refused to pay it back, claiming it was supposed to be food and drink credit. No one had told me this, plus there was nothing left to use it for as everyone‚Äôs bills had been paid (without my knowledge).

No flexibility or apologies from staff on any of this. No other solution given but to order some take out on the rest of the ‚Äúdeposit‚Äù. What had been a lovely celebration ended in disappointment, due to their terrible communication and zero problem-solving skills after their own mistakes.
review 4: bought some of their foods and it was just okay. however, i really like the place, you got small playground for kids and swimming pool.
review 5: We meet here regularly and it is always such a great time getting together. The staff and food are great and the atmosphere is relaxing and nice.
